        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 4:15PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Metamora, or near Lapeer, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Anchorville, Harsens Island, Armada, Capac, Ray Center, Lapeer,
Emmett, New Baltimore, Marine City, Berville, Leonard, St. Clair,
Memphis, Chesterfield Township, Algonac, Almont, Lakeville, Lum,
Adair, and Attica.

This includes the following highways...
I-94 between mile markers 243 and 272.
I-69 between mile markers 150 and 199.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
